Msg_store now supports concurrent reads when it is safe, directly from the queue. This means that even if the msg_store process is flooded with writes or acks, it won't (necessarily) block queues. This is extremely useful and has substantial benefit when memory has been exhausted and the queue is operating off  only (effectively, no message content held in ram).
